name: Chad Beroth
bio: Massachusetts / North Carolina. I paint like a twelve-year-old. Follow for updates. No NFTs.

social_posts.post_text:
NC people! 

Dane has extended the: Emily Beroth “Creature Comforts” show and my “The Self Portrait Show” through the month of December at Delurk@Gallery in Winston Salem, NC! If you couldn’t make it to the opening or to get in to see it in November, it’s opening again tonight at 7pm, and it’ll be there for the rest of the month! Even if you have an overwhelming urge to block your eyes when walking by my weird and creepy self portraits, it’ll be worth it for you to stop in to see Emily’s work. Her new stuff is fantastic! Stop in and check it out! Have a great rest of your day, y’all. 😚😉😊

Birds are returning and flowers are blooming. It’s officially Kitchen Sink season! Woohoo!! 

VISUAL ARTISTS: If you’d like to be a part of Delurk’s juried open-call “The Kitchen Sink” show, follow the link below to submit. (As always, submission and entry is free!)

Good luck, y’all! 

http://www.delurkgallery.com/the-kitchen-sink?fbclid=PAAaZiCD663tLKr2g7NoJ3eie_naJV5dFE-UF8gvZCe5T7tbeYNgLbGw-icjc
